public interface Expression<T>
Base interface for any expression and terms operating on domain objects.

    • evaluate

      Object evaluate(T domainObject, DomainReader<T> domainReader)
      The method that evaluates the expression on a domain object.
      Parameters:
      domainObject - the domain object on which the evaluation is computed
      domainReader - the loose coupling interface for reading data (domain fields and parameters)
      Returns:
      the result of the evaluation. Its java class should be compliant with the type returned by getType().

    • isEditable

      default boolean isEditable()
      Returns:
      true if the expression is editable

    • setValue

      default void setValue(T domainObject, Object value, DomainWriter<T> dataWriter)
      Change the value of the expression (assuming the expression is editable).
      Parameters:
      domainObject - the domain object on which the evaluation is computed
      value - the new value to set. Its java class should be compliant with the type returned by getType().
      dataWriter - the loose coupling interface for writing data (domain fields and parameters)

    • toString

      StringBuilder toString(StringBuilder sb)
      Method called by AbstractExpressions.toString() to optimize the String construct by passing the StringBuilder.
      Parameters:
      sb - The StringBuilder to be used for the String construct
      Returns:
      The StringBuilder so append() methods can be chained

    • getPrecedenceLevel

      int getPrecedenceLevel()
      Returns:
      The precedence level of the expression, which will determine if parenthesis are needed when printing. For example: x * (y + z) => parenthesis because Plus precedence level (=6) < Multiply precedence level (=7)

    • collectPersistentTerms

      default void collectPersistentTerms(List<Expression<T>> persistentTerms)
      This method will collect all persistent terms of the expression and add them into the passed collection. For example, calling this method on 2 * (a + b) will collect a and b.
      Parameters:
      persistentTerms - the collection where persistent terms will be added.
